Iowa has been rolling lately, and is coming off a win against a surging Indiana Hoosiers squad. The Hawkeyes will now square up with the Purdue Boilermakers for the Big 10 Championship. Gametime: 3:30pm EST TV: CBS Live Stream: CBS Sports App, fuboTV, Sling, YouTube TV, Hulu + Live TV Don’t put much stock in Purdue’s regular season sweep of Iowa, given the improbability that the Boilermakers will hit 51 percent of 3-pointers and the Hawkeyes will hit just 27 percent again. No team in the Big Ten has played better than Iowa over the past 3½ weeks, during which it has gone 8-1, while averaging 84.5 points per game. In a shootout featuring two of the best offenses in the nation, ride the hot hand of the Hawkeyes, who have been lighting up far superior defenses lately.